The paper deals with graph theory and optimization, which are common topics in computer science. The use of the Lov\'asz $\vartheta$ function and completely positive programming suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) categories. The geometric insight provided in the paper suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) category. The use of graphs and their properties suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
